# Test Conventions

## Imports

Always use this single import line:

```ts
import { test, expect, request, type Page, type FrameLocator, type Request } from '@playwright/test';
```

## File header

Generated specs begin with the plan + seed reference comments:

```ts
// spec: specs/<plan-file>.md
// seed: tests/seed.spec.ts
```

## Naming

- Test IDs: `TC-<AREA>-<NN>` (e.g. `TC-DB-01` dashboard UI, `TC-DV-01` Dataverse validation).
- `describe` matches the top-level plan item (e.g. `Dashboard Screen`).
- Generated test title matches the scenario name; one test per generated file.
- Include a comment with the plan step text before each step execution.

## Helper functions (reuse; do not reinvent)

- `openDashboard(page)` — navigates to app URL, waits for `Dashboard`, returns `appFrame`.
- `openCreateInvoice(page)` — navigates, clicks Create Invoice, returns `appFrame`.
- `getBillingCycleDates()` — returns `{ start, end }` ISO dates for the current billing cycle.
- `getDataverseCount(token, filterExpression)` — calls Dataverse with filter, returns count.
- `getDashboardTaskCount(page, appFrame, labelPattern)` — reads a numeric count from the
  Invoice Tasks section (the ONLY place `waitForTimeout` is allowed).
- `getLineItemCount(appFrame)` — counts line item rows on the Create Invoice form.

## Assertions

- `expect.soft` for UI structure visibility; hard `expect` for interaction/navigation.
- Prefer regex over literal counts for dynamic values.

## Marked screenshots (evidence)

Every test should capture clear, self-explanatory evidence using the shared utility
`tests/utils/screenshot.ts`. NEVER use `locator.screenshot()` for evidence — it crops to the
element and loses context. Instead:

- `markAndShot(page, target, label, testInfo, options?)` — highlights one element.
- `markGroupAndShot(page, targets, label, testInfo, options?)` — highlights the **union**
  bounding box of several elements (nav strips, card rows, open dropdowns, forms). Prefer this
  when the observation is a group, not a single label.
- `shot(page, label, testInfo)` — a plain full-context screenshot (e.g. an overview shot).

Rules:

- `target` / `targets` must be frame-scoped Locators (`appFrame.getBy...`) so the overlay is
  injected into the iframe and lines up with the element(s).
- Capture AFTER the scenario has loaded (assert visibility first; wait for real data such as a
  numeric count). Do not screenshot a half-loaded screen.
- Scroll the group into view (the helper scrolls first/last anchors) before capturing.
- Prefer **one (or two) group marks per scenario** over many single-label shots.
- Wrap each captured scenario in a `test.step('<label>')` so the report groups the marked image
  under a readable step. Keep the `label` identical between the step and the screenshot.
- The utility settles via `requestAnimationFrame` (no `waitForTimeout`).

```ts
import { markAndShot, markGroupAndShot } from './utils/screenshot';

await test.step('Summary cards', async () => {
  await markGroupAndShot(
    page,
    [totalInvoices, totalPartners, totalProject, totalRevenue],
    'Summary cards',
    testInfo,
  );
});
```
